SIMPLE: hoity-toity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoity-toity
<hw>Hoi"ty-toi`ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Hoit</er>.]</ety> <def>Thoughtless; giddy; flighty; also, haughty;
patronizing; <as>as, to be in <ex>hoity-toity</ex> spirits, or to assume
<ex>hoity-toity</ex> airs</as>; used also as an exclamation, denoting
surprise or disapprobation, with some degree of contempt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Hoity-toity</qex>! What have I to do with dreams?</q>
<rj><qau>Congreve.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hokeday</ent>⟦br⟧
